Model:Class.name: ConsoleControl
Model:Class.annotation: The ConsoleControl class provides a simple text based interface for the game of turn based pacman.

Model:Attribute.name: bi
Model:Attribute.annotation: Buffered input for reading in characters

Model:Operation.name: ConsoleControl
Model:Operation.annotation: Creates a Console Controller for use in the tb-pacman game

Model:Operation.name: execute
Model:Operation.annotation: Simple execution method. If w,a,s or d are pressed pacman will move in it's respective direction. If q is pressed the game will end. @return True if the game is to continue to execute. False if game is complete.

Model:Operation.name: gameOver
Model:Operation.annotation: Should a gameOver Event be broadcast, the controller will end the game.

Model:Operation.name: levelComplete
Model:Operation.annotation: Prompts the player to start a new game when they beat the level. In the full game, this should probably load the next level.

Model:Class.name: PacShell
Model:Class.annotation: PacShell class serves to initialise a test level, and all resources needed to run an instance of turn-based pacman

Model:Class.name: Character
Model:Class.annotation: Character models a game entity, be it human or AI controlled, that resides in and can move around a Maze. This class has methods to move around the maze and to access the maze's tiles. Inheriting classes can implement specific behaviour or characteristics.

Model:Reference.name: tile
Model:Reference.annotation: A reference to the Tile that the Character is occupying.

Model:Operation.name: Character
Model:Operation.annotation: Constructor of objects of type Character.

Model:Operation.name: move
Model:Operation.annotation: Moves the Character one Tile in the desired Direction. @return True if the move was a success. False if it failed (ie. there is no exit in the Direction.

Model:Operation.name: getNeighbour
Model:Operation.annotation: Gets the Tile adjacent to this Character's current Tile in the desired Direction. @return The Tile that the exit in that Direction leads to. Returns null if the exit contains a null reference (a wall in the Maze).

Model:Operation.name: setTile
Model:Operation.annotation: Sets a new Tile as the Character's current position, provided the tile is not null. If the tile is null, nothing occurs and false is returned. @return True if successful.

Model:Operation.name: getTile
Model:Operation.annotation: Gets the tile that the Character currently resides in. @return The current tile.

Model:Class.name: GameModel
Model:Class.annotation: GameModel is the main class of the game's model. It can see and control all aspects of the game, and can notify the view and controller of changes to the game state through its inheritance of the Observable class. Its functions include loading gameLevels from file, loading them up, controlling the game Characters, executing move functions and beginning and ending the game.

Model:Reference.name: player
Model:Reference.annotation: The game's main human controlled Character.

Model:Reference.name: gamelevel
Model:Reference.annotation: The current GameLevel that is loaded.

Model:Attribute.name: levels
Model:Attribute.annotation: A List of all Level files the game can access and load.

Model:Attribute.name: listeners
Model:Attribute.annotation: A list of all listeners to this game object

Model:Operation.name: GameModel
Model:Operation.annotation: Loads a game using the given GameLevel. This function is mostly for testing purposes, as the full game will use a list of file names to generate levels. @param levelListFilename

Model:Operation.name: loadLevel
Model:Operation.annotation: Loads a level from file and loads all of its attributes.

Model:Operation.name: makeMove
Model:Operation.annotation: Makes the Player move in the specified Direction, then immediately calls updateGhosts() to move the ghosts. @return True if the move was executed. False if the move couldn't execute (ie. there is a wall in that direction).

Model:Operation.name: updateGhosts
Model:Operation.annotation: After a Player has moved, this method iterates through the ghosts List and calls upon their update methods (ie. determine direction of travel, then move self.)

Model:Operation.name: stateCheck
Model:Operation.annotation: Checks the various events (player death, level complete) that can happen during the game, and sends events accordingly.

Model:Operation.name: getPlayer
Model:Operation.annotation: @return The Player Character

Model:Operation.name: getGhost
Model:Operation.annotation: @return The Ghost at the specified index.

Model:Operation.name: getNumGhosts
Model:Operation.annotation: @return the number of ghosts currently in the maze.

Model:Operation.name: resetLevel
Model:Operation.annotation: Has the level reset to its initial load state (ie. Characters return start positions, all Tiles have dots put back in them, lives reset.)

Model:Operation.name: addGameListener
Model:Operation.annotation: Adds a game listener to the list of objects listening on this GameModel.

Model:Operation.name: removeGameListener
Model:Operation.annotation: Removes a game listener to the list of objects listening on this GameModel.

Model:Operation.name: getMaze
Model:Operation.annotation: @return The currently loaded Maze.

Model:EnumerationType.name: Direction
Model:EnumerationType.annotation: The Direction enumeration is used to identify the cardinal directions.

Model:Class.name: Maze
Model:Class.annotation: The Maze class stores a grid of game tiles. It includes functionality to add and remove tiles from the grid, and automatically adds and removes the corresponding exits to these tiles. Walls within the maze are simply modelled by the absence of exits. This allows for one sided walls, portals, wrap around and all sorts of other awesomeness. Maze class also supports iteration over the contained tiles.

Model:Reference.name: tile
Model:Reference.annotation: stores the grid of maze tiles, indexed by their x,y coordinates

Model:Attribute.name: maxX
Model:Attribute.annotation: stores the maximum rows in the maze (from 0 to 1 less than this value)

Model:Attribute.name: maxY
Model:Attribute.annotation: stores the maximum columns in the maze (from 0 to 1 less than this value)

Model:Attribute.name: passDots
Model:Attribute.annotation: the required dots remaining to pass the maze

Model:Operation.name: Maze
Model:Operation.annotation: Generates a new maze with the specified maximum size

Model:Operation.name: addTile
Model:Operation.annotation: Adds a new tile to the maze at the specified x, y position, given that the position is currently empty. Automatically adds exits to adjacent tiles. @return true if the add was successful, false if the position is already filled or invalid position passed

Model:Operation.name: removeTile
Model:Operation.annotation: Removes the tile at the specified x, y coordinates @return true if the tile was successfully removed, false if no tile existed at the given position

Model:Operation.name: getTile
Model:Operation.annotation: Returns the tile at the specified x, y coordinates @return null if no tile was found at the specified location or if the index was invalid

Model:Operation.name: getNeighbour
Model:Operation.annotation: Gets the tile neighbouring a given tile in the maze. @return null if no neighbour exists, or the neighbour tile

Model:Operation.name: clearMaze
Model:Operation.annotation: Clears the maze of all tiles.

Model:Operation.name: dotsRemaining
Model:Operation.annotation: @return the number of unvisited tiles (dots) remaining in the maze

Model:Operation.name: isComplete
Model:Operation.annotation: @return true if the maze has the less than or equal to the remaining number of dots required to clear the maze, false if the maze cleared

Model:Operation.name: addExit
Model:Operation.annotation: Adds an exit to the specified tile in the specified direction. Also can add a return exit from the neighbouring tile to the current tile. Requires that another tile already exists in the specified direction. @return false if the add failed for any reason (ie. tile does not exist, neighbour does not exist, exits already exist)

Model:Operation.name: removeExit
Model:Operation.annotation: Removes an exit from the specified tile. Also can remove the return exit from the neighbouring tile to the current tile. Requires that the tile exist, and that it has an exit in the given direction. @return false if the remove failed for any reason (ie. tile does not exist, exits do not exist)

Model:Operation.name: getMaxX
Model:Operation.annotation: @return the maximum x coordinate in this maze (from 0 to maxX - 1)

Model:Operation.name: getMaxY
Model:Operation.annotation: @return the maximum y coordinate in this maze (from 0 to maxY - 1)

Model:Operation.name: setPassDots
Model:Operation.annotation: Sets the number of dots remaining needed to pass the maze

Model:Operation.name: getPassDots
Model:Operation.annotation: @return the number of dots remaining needed to pass the maze

Model:Class.name: GameLevel
Model:Class.annotation: GameLevel contains all the information needed for a complete level for turn based pacman. This includes the game maze itself, as well as the starting tiles for the player and the ghosts

Model:Reference.name: tile
Model:Reference.annotation: stores the starting location of the player

Model:Attribute.name: ghostStarts
Model:Attribute.annotation: stores the starting location of the ghosts

Model:Operation.name: GameLevel
Model:Operation.annotation: Generates a new level with the given maze. This maze should not be replaced once the level object has been created.

Model:Operation.name: isComplete
Model:Operation.annotation: @return true if every tile on the maze has been visited, false if not

Model:Operation.name: getMaze
Model:Operation.annotation: Returns the underlying maze structure. This will most likely be required by the view to draw the game area. @return the underlying maze structure

Model:Operation.name: setPlayerStart
Model:Operation.annotation: Sets the player start to the passed tile. No function if null.

Model:Operation.name: clearPlayerStart
Model:Operation.annotation: Clears the player starting point.

Model:Operation.name: addGhostStart
Model:Operation.annotation: Adds a new ghost starting point.

Model:Operation.name: clearGhostStart
getGhosts
Model:Operation.annotation: @return the number of ghost starts present in the level.

Model:Operation.name: getPlayerStart
Model:Operation.annotation: @return the starting tile of the player, or null if none has been defined

Model:Operation.name: getGhostStart
Model:Operation.annotation: Returns the specified ghost starting point. @return null if invalid index is passed, or a ghost starting tile otherwise

Model:Class.name: Ghost
Model:Class.annotation: A Ghost character. Its main purpose in Turn-Based Pacman is to select and chase another Character type around the Maze.

Model:Reference.name: character
Model:Reference.annotation: The Character that the ghost is meant to chase.

Model:Operation.name: Ghost
Model:Operation.annotation: Constructor for objects of type Ghost. Creates a new Ghost type character.

Model:Operation.name: getNextMove
Model:Operation.annotation: Determines the tile that the ghost should move to next. @return the adjacent tile in the direction the ghost should move in, or null if no move should be made

Model:Class.name: Tile
Model:Class.annotation: Tile class represents one movement square within the game world. Each tile stores a list of neighbouring tiles, as well as a flag which stores whether the tile has been visited by the player or not.

Model:Attribute.name: visited
Model:Attribute.annotation: stores whether the tile has been visited by the player

Model:Attribute.name: xCoord
Model:Attribute.annotation: stores the x coordinate of the tile in relation to the maze grid

Model:Attribute.name: yCoord
Model:Attribute.annotation: stores the y coordinate of the tile in relation to the maze grid

Model:Attribute.name: exits
Model:Attribute.annotation: the list of possible exits from the tile (only cardinal direction allowed)

Model:Operation.name: Tile
Model:Operation.annotation: Constructs a new tile at the given coordinates. The new tile has no neighbours, and has not been visited.

Model:Operation.name: hasDot
Model:Operation.annotation: @return true if the tile has not been visited, false if it has

Model:Operation.name: getXCoord
Model:Operation.annotation: @return the x coordinate of the tile in relation to the maze grid

Model:Operation.name: getYCoord
Model:Operation.annotation: @return the y coordinate of the tile in relation to the maze grid

Model:Operation.name: clearDot
Model:Operation.annotation: Sets the visited status of the tile to true (ie. no dot should be drawn).

Model:Operation.name: resetDot
Model:Operation.annotation: Sets the visited status of the tile to false (ie. a dot should be drawn)

Model:Operation.name: setExit
Model:Operation.annotation: Adds an exit to the tile. An exit may not be added to a direction with an existing exit unless the original exit is removed first. @return returns true if the add was successful, false if a duplicate key was encountered

Model:Operation.name: removeExit
Model:Operation.annotation: Removes a given exit from the tile. @return false if the exit did not exist, true otherwise

Model:Operation.name: getExit
Model:Operation.annotation: Gets the exit in the specified direction. @return returns the tile in the given direction, or null if no exit exists

Model:Operation.name: shortName
Model:Operation.annotation: Returns of a string of the tile's x and y coordinates. Mostly for debug purposes. @return a string in the format of "Tile X:n Y:n"

Model:Operation.name: toString
Model:Operation.annotation: @return a long string description of the tile and it's exits

Model:Class.name: GameEvent
Model:Class.annotation: GameEvent represents an event generated by a GameModel object. This class stores the source GameModel, and can be used to pass additional details on the event.

Model:Reference.name: gamemodel
Model:Reference.annotation: Stores the GameModel that sent this event

Model:Operation.name: GameEvent
Model:Operation.annotation: The eventType is specified upon the object's creation. @param eventType

Model:Operation.name: getSource
Model:Operation.annotation: Returns the source GameModel of the event. @return the source of the event

Model:Class.name: MazeIterator
Model:Class.annotation: MazeIterator allows client classes to iterate through the tiles stored in a maze without any knowledge of the underlying data structure. Tiles are returned in a left to right, top to bottom manner, given that (0,0) is in the top left of the coordinate system, and x and y increase across and down.

Model:Reference.name: tile
Model:Reference.annotation: the reference to the array of tiles

Model:Attribute.name: maxX
Model:Attribute.annotation: the x coordinate boundary for the array

Model:Attribute.name: maxY
Model:Attribute.annotation: the y coordinate boundary for the array

Model:Attribute.name: xPointer
Model:Attribute.annotation: the x coordinate next to be retrieved

Model:Attribute.name: yPointer
Model:Attribute.annotation: the y coordinate next to be retrieved

Model:Operation.name: MazeIterator
Model:Operation.annotation: Constructs a new MazeIterator

Model:Class.name: Player
Model:Class.annotation: A Player type Character. This Character is human controlled.

Model:Attribute.name: lives
Model:Attribute.annotation: The number of lives that a Player has. Zero Lives means game over.

Model:Operation.name: Player
Model:Operation.annotation: Creates a new PLayer object and places it in the Maze.

Model:Operation.name: loseLife
Model:Operation.annotation: Decrement's the number of lives this Player has. @return True if the Player has lost his last life.

Model:Operation.name: getLives
Model:Operation.annotation: Retrieves the number of lives this Player has. @return number of lives.

Model:Operation.name: setLives
Model:Operation.annotation: Sets the players live to the specified value, given that it is positive

Model:Operation.name: isDead
Model:Operation.annotation: Checks the number of lives this Player has and determines if its zero. @return True if there are zero lives left.

Model:Operation.name: setTile
Model:Operation.annotation: Sets a new Tile as the Character's current position, provided the tile is not null. If the tile is null, nothing occurs and false is returned. @return True if successful.

Model:Class.name: GameListenerAdapter
Model:Class.annotation: GameListenerAdapter defines the functions that a class may want implement while listening to the GameModel class. Derived from the GameListener Interface by Alex Craig

Model:Operation.name: playerMove
Model:Operation.annotation: This function will be called whenever the player successfully makes a move. @param GameEvent stores the source and additional details on the event

Model:Operation.name: playerDeath
Model:Operation.annotation: This function will be called whenever the player dies. @param GameEvent stores the source and additional details on the event

Model:Operation.name: gameOver
Model:Operation.annotation: This function will be called if the player loses all their lives. @param GameEvent stores the source and additional details on the event

Model:Operation.name: levelComplete
Model:Operation.annotation: This function will be called when every dot on the grid has been collected. @param GameEvent stores the source and additional details on the event

Model:Class.name: ConsoleView
Model:Class.annotation: The ConsoleView class provides a simple, text based way to visualise the game of turn based pacman. In it's current implementation, this class does not support accurate display of one sided walls and portals. This class is primarily for early game play testing purposes.

Model:Operation.name: ConsoleView
Model:Operation.annotation: Default Constructor

Model:Operation.name: ConsoleView
Model:Operation.annotation: Constructs the ConsolveView, and starts it listening to a given GameModel.

Model:Operation.name: drawMaze
Model:Operation.annotation: Draws a graphical representation of a pacman maze to the console. @param maze the maze to draw

Model:Operation.name: playerMove
Model:Operation.annotation: This function will be called whenever the player successfully makes a move. @param GameEvent stores the source and additional details on the event

Model:Operation.name: playerDeath
Model:Operation.annotation: This function will be called whenever the player dies. @param GameEvent stores the source and additional details on the event

Model:Operation.name: gameOver
Model:Operation.annotation: This function will be called if the player loses all their lives. @param GameEvent stores the source and additional details on the event

Model:Operation.name: levelComplete
Model:Operation.annotation: This function will be called when every dot on the grid has been collected. @param GameEvent stores the source and additional details on the event
